---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Compare', url: '/compare' },
  { name: 'BreederHQ vs Everbreed', url: '/compare/breederhq-vs-everbreed' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Is BreederHQ a good alternative to Everbreed for rabbit breeders?',
    answer: 'It depends on operation shape. Everbreed is rabbits-only, has native iOS and Android apps, and is priced per-rabbit-count from $4.99/month (Start, up to 5 breeders) to $19.99/month (Max, unlimited). Everbreed has approximately 10,000 users per public reports and is the largest rabbit-specific tool in the market. BreederHQ is a multi-species platform (rabbits plus 8 more species) with a transactional public marketplace, per-buyer client portal, per-litter and per-animal financial attribution, rules-based automation across the offspring lifecycle, an embed widget that keeps your own website in sync, printable cage cards for rabbits (plus stall / pen / kennel cards for the other 8 supported species from the same species-aware card generator), a rearing protocol library with shipped system templates and a community sharing surface, and Scout AI that reads lab PDFs and vet invoices. If Everbreed-native workflows (48 ARBA breeds already loaded on their side, per-rabbit-count tiered pricing, or the intra-platform rabbit-to-rabbit-breeder marketplace) matter most, Everbreed is a legitimate rabbits-only pick. If you run rabbits plus another species, or you sell kits to buyers with a professional buyer flow, or you want financial visibility, website integration, and rearing protocols, BreederHQ carries more of the operation.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What does Everbreed cost vs BreederHQ?',
    answer: 'Everbreed has four rabbit-count tiers per apps.apple.com listing verified July 1, 2026: Start at $4.99/month (up to 5 breeding rabbits), Grow at $9.99/month or $95.99/year (up to 20), Plus at $14.99/month or $144.99/year (up to 50), and Max at $19.99/month (unlimited). Trial is 30 days, no credit card. Custom pricing for larger rabbitries or multi-farm accounts. BreederHQ pricing is on our pricing page. Founder discount: FOUNDER50 for 50% off Pro or Enterprise for 12 months (first 100 founders). Everbreed can be cheaper on entry for small rabbitries; BreederHQ is the more comprehensive platform for operations that need marketplace, buyer portal, financial attribution, or multi-species coverage.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does Everbreed support species other than rabbits?',
    answer: 'No. Everbreed is explicitly a rabbit management platform. The website markets to rabbit breeders, the app is called "Everbreed - Rabbit Records," and the pricing tiers count breeding rabbits. If you run rabbits plus other species (goats, chickens, ducks, horses, dogs, cats), Everbreed is not the tool for the other side of your operation. BreederHQ supports nine species in one account.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ have a mobile app?',
    answer: 'Yes. Native iOS and Android apps built on Capacitor, plus responsive web. The mobile app is specifically scoped for on-the-go capture (rabbitry aisle, kindling nest box, feed room, feed store, vet visit, show). Mobile execution matters in this category (see the What Everbreed Users Say section below), and reliability of capture is treated as core infrastructure, not a bonus feature.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does Everbreed have a marketplace or a way to sell kits to buyers?',
    answer: 'Everbreed includes a built-in rabbit marketplace for transfers between Everbreed users, per public product materials. It is intra-platform (rabbit-to-rabbit-breeder). BreederHQ runs a transactional public marketplace at marketplace.breederhq.com that surfaces to any buyer (breeder or pet buyer or working-home buyer or homesteader), with structured listings, waitlist management, deposits, contracts, and a per-buyer client portal. Different scope, different audience reach.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I move my Everbreed records to BreederHQ?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ supports CSV import for animals, pedigrees, and contacts. Rabbit records, pedigrees, and buyer contacts can be imported if Everbreed provides CSV export. Photos and documents need re-upload. There is no one-click migration. Plan a few hours of setup or contact support@breederhq.com for scoping help. If Everbreed\'s export options are limited, raise that with their support before committing either direction.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Is Everbreed a good product?',
    answer: 'For a rabbits-only operation of any size, Everbreed is the most rabbit-specific platform available today, with ~10,000 users and native mobile apps. The product has been in the market for years, has a dedicated rabbit-breeder user base, and continues to iterate. Public reviews reflect both loyal users and users experiencing app-reliability frustration; that is common for mobile-first products, and reliability is a real thing to evaluate during the trial period. This page is not a "we are better at everything" argument. It is the honest version of when each tool is the right pick.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Which is better for a small rabbitry with 10 or fewer breeding rabbits?',
    answer: 'If rabbits are the only species and monthly cost is the primary constraint, Everbreed Grow at $9.99/month or $95.99/year is aggressive pricing. If you also want a public marketplace listing that reaches buyers outside the rabbit-breeder community, or per-buyer client portals for kit buyers, or financial attribution per litter, BreederHQ carries more of the workflow but starts at a higher price. Both are legitimate for that scale.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Which is better for a mixed farm (rabbits + goats + chickens)?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ. One account, one subscription, one login, one mental model. Rabbits, goats, and other supported species (dogs, cats, horses, sheep, alpacas, llamas, cattle) all live in the same account. Everbreed is rabbits-only.'
  }
];

const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "BreederHQ vs Everbreed: The Honest 2026 Comparison for Rabbit Breeders",
  "description": "BreederHQ vs Everbreed compared on pricing, species coverage, mobile apps, marketplace, buyer portal, financial tracking, and automation for rabbit breeders. Publicly verifiable facts, verified July 2026.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "BreederHQ",
    "url": "https://breederhq.com"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "BreederHQ",
    "url": "https://breederhq.com",
    "logo": {
      "@type": "ImageObject",
      "url": "https://breederhq.com/logo.svg"
    }
  },
  "image": "https://breederhq.com/og-image.jpg",
  "datePublished": "2026-07-01",
  "dateModified": "2026-07-01",
  "mainEntityOfPage": {
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "@id": "https://breederhq.com/compare/breederhq-vs-everbreed"
  }
};

// Competitor SoftwareApplication + Review nodes. Named reviewers where the
// source names them (Shawna Adams from Google Play, Lydia H. from the Farmkeep
// comparison); anonymized where the source is anonymous. Aggregated positive-
// review-theme quotes are excluded from the Review graph because they are not
// attributable to a single review under schema.org's Review model.
const competitorReviewGraph = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
      "@id": "https://everbreed.com/#software",
      "name": "Everbreed",
      "alternateName": "Everbreed - Rabbit Records",
      "applicationCategory": "BusinessApplication",
      "applicationSubCategory": "Rabbit Management Software",
      "operatingSystem": "iOS, Android, Web",
      "url": "https://everbreed.com",
      "description": "Rabbit-only breeding management platform with native iOS and Android apps, per-rabbit-count tiered pricing, and an intra-platform rabbit-to-rabbit-breeder marketplace.",
      "offers": [
        {
          "@type": "Offer",
          "name": "Start",
          "price": "4.99",
          "priceCurrency": "USD",
          "description": "Up to 5 breeding rabbits",
          "priceSpecification": {
            "@type": "UnitPriceSpecification",
            "price": "4.99",
            "priceCurrency": "USD",
            "unitCode": "MON"
          },
          "url": "https://apps.apple.com/us/app/everbreed-rabbit-records/id1506912544",
          "availability": "https://schema.org/InStock"
        },
        {
          "@type": "Offer",
          "name": "Grow",
          "price": "9.99",
          "priceCurrency": "USD",
          "description": "Up to 20 breeding rabbits",
          "priceSpecification": {
            "@type": "UnitPriceSpecification",
            "price": "9.99",
            "priceCurrency": "USD",
            "unitCode": "MON"
          },
          "url": "https://apps.apple.com/us/app/everbreed-rabbit-records/id1506912544",
          "availability": "https://schema.org/InStock"
        },
        {
          "@type": "Offer",
          "name": "Plus",
          "price": "14.99",
          "priceCurrency": "USD",
          "description": "Up to 50 breeding rabbits",
          "priceSpecification": {
            "@type": "UnitPriceSpecification",
            "price": "14.99",
            "priceCurrency": "USD",
            "unitCode": "MON"
          },
          "url": "https://apps.apple.com/us/app/everbreed-rabbit-records/id1506912544",
          "availability": "https://schema.org/InStock"
        },
        {
          "@type": "Offer",
          "name": "Max",
          "price": "19.99",
          "priceCurrency": "USD",
          "description": "Unlimited breeding rabbits",
          "priceSpecification": {
            "@type": "UnitPriceSpecification",
            "price": "19.99",
            "priceCurrency": "USD",
            "unitCode": "MON"
          },
          "url": "https://apps.apple.com/us/app/everbreed-rabbit-records/id1506912544",
          "availability": "https://schema.org/InStock"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@type": "Review",
      "itemReviewed": { "@id": "https://everbreed.com/#software" },
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Shawna Adams" },
      "datePublished": "2026-01-16",
      "reviewBody": "The app is glitch-y and oddly particular about movement. For example, you can't touch the actual phone back button or it kicks you out of the app... It also takes a while to sync changes, leading you to think that the changes didn't 'take' resulting in multiple entries.",
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Google Play", "url": "https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.barntrax.hutch" },
      "url": "https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.barntrax.hutch"
    },
    {
      "@type": "Review",
      "itemReviewed": { "@id": "https://everbreed.com/#software" },
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Anonymous Apple App Store reviewer" },
      "datePublished": "2021-12-23",
      "reviewBody": "I love this app but it's so difficult to put my information in because it constantly crashes",
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Apple App Store", "url": "https://apps.apple.com/us/app/everbreed-rabbit-records/id1506912544" },
      "url": "https://apps.apple.com/us/app/everbreed-rabbit-records/id1506912544"
    },
    {
      "@type": "Review",
      "itemReviewed": { "@id": "https://everbreed.com/#software" },
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Anonymous user" },
      "reviewBody": "When you hit the 10+ breeders it doubles in price and you can't use the finance features unless you use the top tier",
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Everbreed blog", "url": "https://everbreed.com/blog/farmkeep-vs-everbreed-which-rabbitry-tool-is-best/" },
      "url": "https://everbreed.com/blog/farmkeep-vs-everbreed-which-rabbitry-tool-is-best/"
    },
    {
      "@type": "Review",
      "itemReviewed": { "@id": "https://everbreed.com/#software" },
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Lydia H." },
      "reviewBody": "I used to use Everbreed for my rabbits, but as my farm grew, it became too expensive and couldn't track everything I wanted... I needed something that worked for rabbits, ducks, goats, chickens, and my market stand",
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Farmkeep", "url": "https://www.farmkeep.com/farm-guides/reviews/farmkeep-vs-everbreed" },
      "url": "https://www.farmkeep.com/farm-guides/reviews/farmkeep-vs-everbreed"
    }
